main event: A witness observed a circular, green, and maneuverable object in the sky for approximately 15 seconds on July 16, 1957.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at 7:55 PM on July 16, 1957., The object was described as being circular and green., The witness commented that the outer haze of Orion stars was not visible at the time., The observed object appeared larger than usual stars and had flashing lights., The report indicates that the sighting could be possibly categorized as a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon.
witness description: observer who saw the object and reported it
